                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15205763" author="ram_krish" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 04:19:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes. But reusing BBpool even offheap though is reducing the GC cycle it is adding to the GC time. We are in the process of analysing this part. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15205773" author="eclark" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 04:30:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Most of the times we&apos;ve tried to share/reuse buffers on the heap things have been much slower on a newer jdk/gc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15205779" author="stack" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 04:41:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So, less GC but GC takes more time?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15205780" author="stack" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 04:43:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How is this different to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-14490&quot; title=&quot;[RpcServer] reuse request read buffer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-14490&quot;&gt;HBASE-14490&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15206011" author="anoop.hbase" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 08:50:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Same idea as in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-14490&quot; title=&quot;[RpcServer] reuse request read buffer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-14490&quot;&gt;HBASE-14490&lt;/a&gt; I believe..&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ya the reuse of the buffers reduces the GCs frequency.  But the avg pause time is increased.  We are working in this area now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15206013" author="anoop.hbase" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 08:51:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is not with G1GC.  With our default GC settings.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15209721" author="ram_krish" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2016 04:25:35 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;But the avg pause time is increased. We are working in this area now.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The recent analysis indicates that this avg pause time is increasing for cases where we have huge number of cells (approx 1k cells) in a row. There is something that happens here such that the cells are getting promoted to the old gen and hence the ParNEw allocation failure time is more. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
